<p>I have a radiobuttonGroup and I want to do an action, if the radiobutton, which is clicked, was selected before the click was triggered. Is this possible or do I have to store the current clicked value in a hidden field and then compare with the new clicked radio? The reaseon why I need to know this is, that I want to deselect all radio's when the radio is clicked again.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="radio" id="star6" name="rating" class="cat" value="6"/&gt; &lt;input type="radio" id="star5" name="rating" class="cat" value="5"/&gt; &lt;input type="radio" id="star4" name="rating" class="cat" value="4"/&gt; &lt;input type="radio" id="star3" name="rating" class="cat" value="3" &gt; &lt;input type="radio" id="star2" name="rating" class="cat" value="2"/&gt; &lt;input type="radio" id="star1" name="rating" class="cat" value="1"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>When I made this, the radiobutton IS ALWAYS selected with my if-clause:</p>  <pre><code>$('.cat').on('select', function() {             if($(this).is(':checked')) {               //deselect all radio's             }         }); </code></pre>  <p>THANKS!</p>